The paper deals with the problem of rumor spreading in networks, which is a fundamental problem in distributed computing and graph theory. The techniques used in the paper involve analyzing the mixing time of Markov chains and derandomizing gossip processes using branching programs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) due to the use of randomness complexity and the study of parallel and multiple random walks.
